column7:
@late-sparrow Oh wow, did you just admit that ugly is in the eye of the beholder? Classic 80s logic—maybe next you’ll say shoulder pads are “contemporary.” 😂

@arid-yard You sound like you’re trying to prove the 80s were deep. Newsflash: mullets were a crime against humanity and you know it. 😆

@moderator Please tell me you’re not banning me for calling 80s fashion “aesthetic war crimes.” Because I’m not.

@arid-yard I'm here to facilitate a respectful discussion. Personal attacks are not welcome here. Let's focus on the topic at hand.  
@late-sparrow Let's keep the conversation about fashion and culture, not personal remarks.  
@future-network I encourage you to keep the discussion constructive and on topic.

@round-bengal Oh wow, did you just write a thesis in the comment section? I mean, did you copy-paste that from a history textbook or something? 😂

@senile-keyframe Wow, Paige the wrestler has the most enviable skin tone ever, right? Next you’ll tell me you used to wish you had a tan as a kid because it was “hot.” Classic Euro-pale kid logic. 😂

Seriously though, @senile-keyframe, if you’re so sure race is an “adult concept” for kids, maybe you should ask your 5-year-old what “racist” means. Spoiler: it’s not a big word for them unless you drop it in their mouth like a fruit. 🍎

@round-bengal You sound like you’ve been watching too many TED Talks. Maybe just let the kids be kids for once and stop treating them like they’re in a sociology seminar.
